Kenya faces a plastic bag crisis, with 2 million bags distributed in Nairobi yearly, leading to environmental and health risks.
The United Nations Environment Programme calls for a ban on plastic bags and a levy on thicker ones.
Eritrea has already taken steps to ban plastic bags, while San Francisco and Los Angeles consider charging fees for bags.
Rwanda and Uganda are also cracking down on plastic bags, with Rwanda already imposing a ban.
Tanzania is set to open a recycling plant to tackle plastic waste.
The push to reduce plastic bag usage is gaining momentum across Africa.
